comment.body:
careless full review > careful partial (half) review
you get to see all the code so you have a better chance of finding meaningful bugs with the context insight you get, while with a partial review you might miss bugs in plain sight because they are not a bug in the portion of code one reviews:
```
int* seconds = (int*) malloc(sizeof(int)*7);
seconds[2] = 4;
printf("%d\n\n", seconds[2]);
free(seconds);
```
This could be better but is not a bug on itself, until you attempt to use `seconds` further down the code, in such case it would be bad but you aren't aware that said variable should still be left allocated...
